The paper discusses the use of bio-inspired solutions for cybersecurity, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The authors also mention the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the need for improved software engineering (cs.SE) in the development of cyber-defense systems. The paper also touches upon the use of sensors and network infrastructure (cs.NI) in detecting and preventing cyber attacks. Finally, the authors discuss the need for a holistic approach to cybersecurity, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
